title: Independent candidate Nazeer Ahmed Abbasi wins PK-42 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Nazeer Ahmed Abbasi has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-42, Abbottabad-I by securing 35,443 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate Sardar Farid Ahmed Khan who bagged 27,623 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 44.79 per cent.
